HEADWORD: Air pocket
<hw>Air" pock"et</hw> <pr>(p⟦ocr⟧k"⟦ecr⟧t)</pr>.
<fld>(aeronautics)</fld> <def>A local region in the atmosphere having a
downward movement and offering less than normal support for the
sustaining surfaces of a flying machine, causing an airplane to drop
suddenly. Same as <altname>air hole</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Air poise</ent>⟦br⟧
